<p class="help-title">Requirements &amp; Recommended Configuration</p>
<hr color="#000000" size="1">
<p class="help-body">All versions of Ultimate Survey ASP are 100% script based, 
so no DLLs or other objects are required to be installed on the web server, with 
the exception of a mail object if your web server does not already have one 
available.</p>
<p class="help-body">In order to run Ultimate Survey ASP on your server, you 
must meet the minimum requirements:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
  <p class="help-body">Web Server running Microsoft Internet Information Server 
  version 4.0 or above with full support for Active Server Pages (ASP).</li>
  <li>
  <p class="help-body">Microsoft Access 97 or above OR SQL Server 7.0 or above.
  </li>
  <li>
  <p class="help-body">Basic knowledge of installing web pages and managing IIS.</li>
  <li>
  <p class="help-body">CDONTS, AspMail, and Jmail components supported for email 
  functionality.</li>
</ul>
<p class="help-body">For best performance, we recommend the following 
configuration:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
  <p class="help-body">Web server running Microsoft Internet Information Server 
  version 5.0 or higher.</li>
  <li>
  <p class="help-body">Microsoft SQL Server 2000.</li>
  <li>
  <p class="help-body">CDONTS for email (This is the built in Microsoft mail 
  component. Most hosts provide this by default, but there are some that do not)</li>
</ul>
<p class="help-body">&nbsp;</p>

